 of vehicle system is being serviced?", "List all necessary components for repair."]}]$__MD__$::jsonb, visual_diagrams = $__MD__$[{"type": "block diagram", "description": "Vehicle Brake System Diagram", "labels": ["Master Cylinder", "Brake Calipers", "Wheel Cylinders"]}, {"type": "flowchart", "description": "Engine Repair Process Diagram", "labels": ["Remove Intake Manifold", "Inspect Engine Block", "Replace Piston Rings"]}]$__MD__$::jsonb WHERE id = 200021;
UPDATE module_lessons SET written_steps = $__MD__$# Systems & Components - Part 2

## Safety Precautions
1. Ensure the vehicle is parked on a level surface and apply the parking brake.
2. Engage the transmission in park (automatic) or first gear (manual).
3. Turn off the engine and all accessories.
4. Wear protective gloves and safety glasses.

## Verification Checklist
1. Check the battery terminals for corrosion.
2. Verify the coolant level is at the recommended maximum.
3. Inspect the brake pads for wear.
4. Check the tire pressure against the manufacturer's recommendations.
5. Verify the oil level is at the recommended minimum.
6. Check the air filter for cleanliness.

## System and Component Inspection
1. Inspect the belts and hoses for signs of wear or damage.
2. Check the condition of the spark plugs.
3. Verify the proper functioning of the cooling system.
4. Check the brake fluid level.
5. Inspect the exhaust system for leaks.
6. Verify the proper functioning of the suspension system.$__MD__$, audio_script = $__MD__$Welcome to Systems & Components - Part 2. In this lesson, we'll be discussing the safety precautions and verification checklist for inspecting various vehicle systems. Please ensure you follow all safety guidelines when working with vehicles. First, let's go over the safety precautions. Make sure the vehicle is parked on a level surface, engage the parking brake, turn off the engine, and wear protective gear. Now, let's move on to the verification checklist. Check the battery terminals for corrosion, verify the coolant level, inspect the brake pads, check the tire pressure, and more. Next, we'll be discussing the system and component inspection. Inspect the belts and hoses, check the spark plugs, verify the cooling system, and more. Remember to always follow proper safety procedures when working with vehicles.$__MD__$, practice_activities = $__MD__$[{"type": "scenario", "title": "Scenario: Vehicle Inspection", "description": "A customer brings in their vehicle for a routine inspection. The technician notices that the brake pads are worn down to 1/8 of an inch. What should the technician do next?", "questions": [{"question": "What is the minimum thickness recommended for brake pads?", "answer": "1/4 inch"}, {"question": "What should the technician recommend to the customer?", "answer": "Replace the brake pads with new ones."}]}]$__MD__$::jsonb, visual_diagrams = $__MD__$[{"type": "block diagram", "description": "Cooling System Diagram", "labels": ["Radiator", "Water Pump", "Thermostat"]}, {"type": "flowchart", "description": "Brake System Diagram", "labels": ["Master Cylinder", "Brake Lines", "Wheel Cylinders"]}]$__MD__$::jsonb WHERE id = 200022;
